{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XKPoMhDgr2jevynnBV847X","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Tmkag7h9zYtv1Nhrw1uwFo","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n ray create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"RAY CLUSTER CONFIGURATION AUDIT REPORT\nNamespace: ray\nAudit Date: 2026-06-24\nAuditor: Read-only automated audit (no cluster changes made)\n\n================================================================\n1. WORKER REPLICA COUNT\n================================================================\nDeployment: ray-worker\n  spec.replicas: 1\n  readyReplicas: 1\n  availableReplicas: 1\n  Status: 1/1 Ready\n\nDeployment: ray-head\n  spec.replicas: 1\n  readyReplicas: 1\n  Status: 1/1 Ready\n\nNote: Worker replica count is at minimum (1). The task context indicates\nworkers may have been scaled up; current state shows a single worker pod.\n\n================================================================\n2. IMAGE VERSIONS\n================================================================\nray-head:   rayproject/ray:2.9.0\nray-worker: rayproject/ray:2.9.0\n\nBoth deployments are pinned to the same image tag (2.9.0), which is\nconsistent. However, Ray 2.9.0 was released in early 2024 and is\nsignificantly behind current upstream releases as of mid-2026.\n\n================================================================\n3. RESOURCE REQUESTS / LIMITS\n================================================================\nray-head container:\n  requests: (none defined)\n  limits:   (none defined)\n  resources field: {}\n\nray-worker container:\n  requests: (none defined)\n  limits:   (none defined)\n  resources field: {}\n\nDEVIATION: Neither deployment specifies CPU or memory requests/limits.\nThis means pods run with BestEffort QoS class and can consume unbounded\nnode resources, which is a compliance concern for production workloads.\n\n================================================================\n4. RAY START FLAGS (COMMAND CONFIGURATION)\n================================================================\nray-head command:\n  ray start --head\n            --node-ip-address=\\${MY_POD_IP}\n            --port=6379\n            --include-dashboard=false\n            --num-cpus=0\n            --block\n\nray-worker command:\n  ray start --address=ray-head:6379\n            --node-ip-address=\\${MY_POD_IP}\n            --num-cpus=1\n            --block\n\nDEVIATION: Dashboard is explicitly disabled (--include-dashboard=false).\nThe head node advertises 0 CPUs to the scheduler (--num-cpus=0), which\nis intentional to prevent task scheduling on the head node but is a\nnon-default configuration choice.\n\n================================================================\n5. EXPOSED SERVICES\n================================================================\nService: ray-head\n  Type:       ClusterIP\n  ClusterIP:  10.96.215.162\n  Ports:\n    - name: gcs  port: 6379  protocol: TCP  targetPort: 6379\n  ExternalIP: <none>\n\nNo NodePort or LoadBalancer services found.\nNo dashboard port (default 8265) is exposed on the Service.\nNo metrics port (default 8080) is exposed on the Service.\n\nDEVIATION: Only the GCS port (6379) is exposed. Since the dashboard is\ndisabled in the head command, the absence of port 8265 on the Service\nis consistent, but confirms zero external observability surface.\n\n================================================================\n6. ACTIVE CONFIGMAPS\n================================================================\nkube-root-ca.crt  (system-managed, 1 key, age ~34s at audit time)\n\nNo custom ConfigMaps exist in the ray namespace. Cluster configuration\nis entirely driven by inline command flags in the Deployment specs.\n\n================================================================\n7. PODS IN NAMESPACE\n================================================================\nray-head-5c586c8fd6-zjh69     1/1 Running  Node: karma-5-control-plane\nray-worker-7d7d685797-qrgrv   1/1 Running  Node: karma-5-control-plane\nray-client                    1/1 Running  Node: karma-5-control-plane\n\nAll pods are scheduled on a single node (karma-5-control-plane).\nA ray-client pod is present and running; this is not part of the\nstandard head/worker Deployment set and warrants awareness.\n\n================================================================\n8. DEVIATIONS FROM DEFAULT/BASELINE SUMMARY\n================================================================\n[DEVIATION-1] resources: {} on both Deployments\n  Impact: BestEffort QoS; no CPU/memory guarantees; risk of OOM eviction\n  or noisy-neighbor interference. Set explicit requests and limits.\n\n[DEVIATION-2] Ray image version 2.9.0 is outdated\n  Impact: Missing ~2 years of bug fixes and security patches upstream.\n  Evaluate upgrade to a current supported release.\n\n[DEVIATION-3] Dashboard disabled (--include-dashboard=false)\n  Impact: No built-in observability UI for jobs, actors, or cluster state.\n  If monitoring is required, re-enable with appropriate auth controls.\n\n[DEVIATION-4] Head node with --num-cpus=0\n  Impact: Head node cannot accept actor/task scheduling. Intentional\n  isolation pattern, but reduces available cluster capacity.\n\n[DEVIATION-5] Single-node placement for all pods\n  Impact: No fault-domain separation; a single node failure loses the\n  entire cluster including the head. Use pod anti-affinity rules or\n  multi-node setup for production.\n\n[DEVIATION-6] No ConfigMaps for cluster configuration\n  Impact: All config is embedded in Deployment command strings, making\n  configuration changes require Deployment edits rather than ConfigMap\n  updates. Consider externalizing key parameters.\n\n================================================================\n9. COMPLIANCE NOTES AND RECOMMENDATIONS\n================================================================\nCRITICAL:\n  - Define resource requests and limits on all containers (DEVIATION-1).\n    Without them, the cluster cannot be admitted by LimitRange policies\n    and violates typical resource-governance requirements.\n\nHIGH:\n  - Plan an image upgrade from 2.9.0 to a supported Ray release (DEVIATION-2).\n    Coordinate with the team during the next change window.\n\nMEDIUM:\n  - Evaluate dashboard enablement with authenticated access for\n    operational visibility (DEVIATION-3).\n  - Add pod anti-affinity or node selectors to spread head/worker across\n    failure domains (DEVIATION-5).\n\nLOW:\n  - Externalize configuration into a ConfigMap to improve auditability\n    and reduce blast radius of Deployment edits (DEVIATION-6).\n  - Document the purpose of the ray-client pod; confirm it is expected.\n\n================================================================\nEND OF AUDIT — NO CHANGES WERE MADE TO THE CLUSTER\n================================================================\"\n","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with audit findings"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2504,"cache_read_input_tokens":30785,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2504},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"531ca376-c2ea-4326-82da-1fa85595d2e9","uuid":"a658d4c5-d70d-40bc-929f-73fd2d7d9d80","request_id":"req_011CcMVijd13qvb3PY7qb8Vw"}
